  "caption": "Comment “Loft” for a Google Map link of the store!\n\nIf you’re already shopped at Donki or the Beams store and want another spot for cool gifts, don’t forget to check out LOFT!\n\nIf Donki is the Walmart of Japan, LOFT is more like the Target of Japan. Cleaner aesthetic, better merchandising, and higher quality products. \n\nThis six floor building has a great selection of stationery, home goods, beauty/skincare, watches, and travel bags so come here if you’re looking for those. The quality is a step up, and you’ll products at all price points!\n—\n#tokyogift #tokyostyle #tokyotravel #traveling #traveljapan #fashion #madeinjapan #japanesegifts",
  "transcript": "If you're looking for a place with different price points for gifts, this is the place to go. If Donkey is considered the Walmart of Japan, Loft is target. Cleaner merchandising and higher quality products. We're here at Loft in Shibuya and you have 7 floors packed with so many cool things so let me show you what it looks like. Starting off with Floor B1 where they have a ton of stationary products including my favorite Pilot juice up pens, stickers and notebooks. Next we're on the beauty floor where you'll find a variety of J&K beauty products at great prices and yes they do tax free here. Third floor we have home goods where I saw some incredible teapots, coffee accessories and bento boxes made in Japan. Fourth floor we have interior goods like clocks, lamps and furniture. Just be sure to check compatibility if you're buying anything electric. Fifth floor we have bags and travel goods where you'll find luggage and made in Japan travel here. The last floor is mainly for tourists where you can receive your tax refund in cash but they also have small goods like smith skis and blind boxes here. Thanks for watching. If you love fashion, lifestyle and Japanese culture, don't forget to follow.",
